\end_inset

A simpler method to achieve the same would be to detect shapes on the separate
 clusters after determining them using the kmeans algorithm.
 The OpenCV library already implements the necessary methods for detecting
 contours.
 The relevant clusters will be converted into a blured grayscale image and
 the saturation will be adjusted to get a better thresholding to convert
 it into a binary image, which will then be used to detect the edges.
 The method 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

findContours(...)
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 will provide the corresponding contours, if there are several contours
 convoluted in each other as for example seen in Fig 3.2 only the most outer
 one is relevant and will represent a cluster.
 In the case of Fig 3.2 the only relevant contours are labeled 0-2, because
 the remaining contours are all enclosed in contour 2.
 
\end_layout

